<p>I think the major improvements come to play in the articles, themselves.
Some of the changes are subtle but make a big difference. The line length was
shortened to reduce eye strain. The headings were given styles that allowed
them to be more distinct from each other. We now have a range of headings that
provide different emphasis, which reinforces the hierarchy of the article
content.</p>

<figure>
  <img src="images/portfolio/robots/04.png">
</figure>
<p>Before our redesign, you can see that the information is grouped and
organized, but it's a little difficult to know where my eye should go first.
Instead of using a two-column layout to separate the author information and
meta-info from the article, we consolidated this into a single-column layout
(see image below). This allows your eye to flow in a more familiar pattern,
top-down, to read the article.</p>
